<subSubSection id="C314C29CFF82CD41C6A15AD1FBF6E150" pageId="2" pageNumber="591" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB19117FF82CD41C6A15AD1FBF6E150" blockId="2.[151,1437,684,2043]" pageId="2" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="B97A4D05FF82CD41C6A15AD1FEE9E099" bold="true" box="[151,274,684,710]" pageId="2" pageNumber="591">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing medium size, CP short, reaching anterior margin basal of the fusion point of CuPaα and M+CuA, ScA and ScP with numerous branches, R forking into RA and RP after ScP reaching anterior margin, MP originating after ScA reaching anterior margin, CuPa much longer than CuPaα.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
