<subSubSection id="C314C29CFF83CD40C6F15AF2FA8CE1DE" pageId="3" pageNumber="592" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB19117FF83CD40C6F15AF2FA8CE1DE" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,897]" pageId="3" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis id="B97A4D05FF83CD40C6F15AF2FEC0E0F6" bold="true" box="[199,315,655,681]" pageId="3" pageNumber="592">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species can be assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EEA94FF83CD40C4E15AF2FCBEE0F6" authorityName="Handlirsch" authorityYear="1906" box="[727,837,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Elcanidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Elcaninae">Elcaninae</taxonomicName>
by its relatively narrow area between RA and RP, and CuPaβ, CuPb, and AA1 fused with each other. It falls in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EEA94FF83CD40C5145ACEFB80E092" authority="Westwood, 1854" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1854" box="[802,1147,690,717]" class="Insecta" family="Elcanidae" genus="Panorpidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97A4D05FF83CD40C5145ACEFC4DE092" box="[802,950,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="592">Panorpidium</emphasis>
Westwood, 1854
</taxonomicName>
because of the following characters: few branched ScA; three longitudinal branches between basal part of RP and CuA+CuPaα; and CuPaβ, CuPb and AA1 fused with each other distally (
<figureCitation id="13358D92FF83CD40C49C5A86FCDCE14A" box="[682,807,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1836,1860]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,921,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-386@3.[151,1436,921,1813]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Panorpidium acusicaudum sp. nov., holotype, CNU-ORT-LB2011041P/C.A and B. Photo and interpretive drawing of habitus, C. Interpretive drawing of left forewing, D. Interpretive drawing of right forewing, E. Interpretive drawing of left hindwing, F. Interpretive drawing of right hindwing, G. Details of left middle leg, H. Details of left metatibia and metatarsus, I. Details of left fore leg, J. Details of the end of abdomen and ovipositor. Scale bar for A and B = 10 mm, C-H and J = 2 mm, I = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480114/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="592">Fig. 2C–D</figureCitation>
). The new species can be distinguished from 
<emphasis id="B97A4D05FF83CD40C3125A86FEBFE166" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="592">
<taxonomicName id="4C0EEA94FF83CD40C3125A86FA62E14B" authorityName="Gorochov, Jarzembowski and Coram" authorityYear="2006" box="[1316,1433,763,788]" class="Insecta" family="Elcanidae" genus="Panorpidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvum">P. parvum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EEA94FF83CD40C6A15B62FEBFE166" authorityName="Gorochov, Jarzembowski and Coram" authorityYear="2006" box="[151,324,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Elcanidae" genus="Panorpidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculatum">P. bimaculatum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EEA94FF83CD40C74E5B62FE36E167" authorityName="Kim, Lee, Nam and Park" authorityYear="2021" box="[376,461,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Elcanidae" genus="Panorpidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spica">
<emphasis id="B97A4D05FF83CD40C74E5B62FE36E167" box="[376,461,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="592">P. spica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the large size of body and wings, shorter CP with fewer branches, straight and longer CuPa and different pattern of coloration. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EEA94FF83CD40C5385B3EFC53E102" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1854" box="[782,936,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Elcanidae" genus="Panorpidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tessellatum">
<emphasis id="B97A4D05FF83CD40C5385B3EFC53E102" box="[782,936,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="592">P. tessellatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EEA94FF83CD40C5815B3EFBBFE103" authorityName="Gorochov, Jarzembowski and Coram" authorityYear="2006" box="[951,1092,835,860]" class="Insecta" family="Elcanidae" genus="Panorpidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="proximum">
<emphasis id="B97A4D05FF83CD40C5815B3EFBBFE103" box="[951,1092,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="592">P. proximum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EEA94FF83CD40C2645B3EFB23E102" authorityName="Sharov" authorityYear="1968" box="[1106,1240,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Elcanidae" genus="Panorpidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricum">
<emphasis id="B97A4D05FF83CD40C2645B3EFB23E102" box="[1106,1240,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="592">P. sibiricum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EEA94FF83CD40C2D05B3EFA85E103" authorityName="Fang, Wang, Zhang, Wang, Jarzembowski, Zheng, Zhang, Lia and Liu" authorityYear="2015" box="[1254,1406,835,860]" class="Insecta" family="Elcanidae" genus="Panorpidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yixianensis">
<emphasis id="B97A4D05FF83CD40C2D05B3EFA85E103" box="[1254,1406,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="592">P. yixianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in CP with fewer branches, wider area between ScP and R, few branches of RP and different pattern of coloration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
